When an atom emits an **alpha particle (α)**, its atomic number decreases by 2 (changing the element), but when it emits a **beta particle (β⁻ or β⁺)**, the atomic number changes by ±1 (also altering the element). Thus, emission of either particle **may** (but not always) result in a different element.
